## Post-Install Validation Checklist

Run all checks immediately after installation or patching. Do not declare the installation complete until every section below is confirmed.

---

### 1. Service Checks

```powershell
Get-Service MSSQLSERVER,'Teamcenter Server Manager TCFISHER_PoolA',W3SVC
```

| Service | Expected status |
|---------|----------------|
| `MSSQLSERVER` | `Running` |
| `Teamcenter Server Manager TCFISHER_PoolA` | `Running` |
| `W3SVC` | `Running` |

---

### 2. Port Checks

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -State Listen |
  Where-Object LocalPort -in 80,1433,8086,8087,8088,3000,4544 |
  Sort-Object LocalPort
```

| Port | Service |
|------|---------|
| `80` | IIS web tier |
| `1433` | SQL Server |
| `8086` | Server Manager assignment service |
| `8087` | Server Manager MUX |
| `8088` | Server Manager JMX/RMI |
| `3000` | AWC gateway (if in scope) |
| `4544` | FSC (if FMS is in scope) |

---

### 3. IIS Checks

```powershell
Import-Module WebAdministration
Get-Website
Get-WebApplication
```

Expected:
- `Default Web Site` — State: `Started`
- `/tc` application — present

---

### 4. Teamcenter URL Checks

```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest http://server2019tc/tc/services/ServiceDispatcher?wsdl -UseBasicParsing
Invoke-WebRequest http://server2019tc:3000/ -UseBasicParsing
Invoke-WebRequest http://server2019tc:3000/tc.html -UseBasicParsing
```

| URL | Expected |
|-----|----------|
| `http://server2019tc/tc/services/ServiceDispatcher?wsdl` | `StatusCode 200` |
| `http://server2019tc:3000/` | `StatusCode 200` (AWC gateway, if in scope) |
| `http://server2019tc:3000/tc.html` | `StatusCode 200` (AWC, if in scope) |

> **Expected non-error behavior:** `http://server2019tc/tc` redirects to `/tc/` which returns IIS `403.14`. This is normal — the bare `/tc/` directory is not the AWC entry page on this host. Use `:3000/` and `:3000/tc.html` as the real AWC entrypoints.

---

### 5. Filesystem Checks

```powershell
@(
  "C:\TC2412",
  "C:\tcdata",
  "C:\TC2412\install\configuration.xml",
  "C:\TC2412\pool_manager\confs\TCFISHER",
  "C:\TC2412\net_webtier_TCFISHER\tc"
) | ForEach-Object { [pscustomobject]@{ Path = $_; Exists = (Test-Path $_) } }
```

All paths must return `True`.

---

### 6. Configuration Version Check

```powershell
Select-String "version" C:\TC2412\install\configuration.xml | Select-Object -First 5
```

After base install: version `2412`
After patch: version `2412.8`

---

### 7. TEM Recovery State Check

```powershell
cmd /c "C:\TC2412\install\tem.bat -restart -config=TCFISHER -test"
```

Expected:
```
Configuration TCFISHER is not in recovery mode
```

If TEM still reports recovery mode, follow `notes/2026-04-16_tem_stale_recovery_state_cleanup.md` before proceeding.
